I don’t know why this happens and I wish that the world we lived in was different…⁠
⁠
But, it isn’t. ⁠

⁠
💬 We are taught to that who we are in inherently ⁠
"not good enough" ⁠
💬 We are taught to conform.⁠
💬 We are so afraid of being shunned...that we don’t put ourselves out there.⁠
⁠
As a result, we all consistently undervalue our ideas, our thoughts, and the impact that we can have on the world around us.⁠
⁠
I want you to break free from these mental chains - don’t you dare diminish your voice because you don’t believe that anyone would want to listen to you!⁠
⁠
You are unique and powerful as you are and I hope that you start to believe in that. 🔥⁠
⁠
for instance, if I listened to all the haters who told me that my hair was "unprofessional" and needed to be "tamed"...⁠
⁠
❎ I would’ve never started my natural hair journey. ⁠
❎ I would’ve never started my YouTube channel.⁠
❎ I would’ve never taken the opportunity to start my coaching business. ⁠
⁠
I certainly would not be making this post right now. ⁠

I know how hard it is to put yourself out there but if you don’t...then you let "them" win. ⁠

Trust me, if you start to say NO to the haters one at a time...eventually you won’t even hear their voices anymore. ⁠

In my stories, I've talked about how I outsourced my meal planning, grocery ordering and Christmas gift shopping to virtual assistants - who knew it would get such a big response!⁠
⁠
⁠Support is NOT a luxury - it is a necessity for women in business! In fact, it's a cultural *double standard* to expect women to "do it all." ⁠
⁠
⁠The truth is, we need to normalize receiving SUPPORT as women, *especially* as business women.⁠
⁠
This is why I urge entrepreneurial women to prioritize: ⁠
⁠
⁠1) Building a business around a high-income, in-demand skill (because yes, support costs money)⁠
2) Choosing a business model that generates consistent, repeatable revenue (because yes, support cost money every month)⁠
⁠
⁠As the person that makes both your business and your *household* go 'round, you can't afford to be stressed out and worried about your next sale or client.⁠
⁠
Not only repeatable revenue allow you to cover your business expenses (obviously!) with ease, but it allows you to bring on consistent support in your personal life (i.e. hiring a housekeeper or paying a meal planning service) so that you can show up refreshed and relaxed for your customers and your family.⁠
⁠
My goal is to have it all, not DO it all. 🤷🏾‍♀️ #sorrynotsorry⁠
⁠
Drop a 🙌🏾 in the comments if you agree!

If I could go back in time and tell myself on thing when I first went full-time in my business, it'd definitely be this.⁠
⁠
Why?⁠
⁠
Because when I was first getting started, I was so excited about making 6-figures on my own that I paid no attention to HOW I was doing it.⁠
⁠
At the time, I was a newlywed with no kids and had no problem⁠ launching new stuff all the time or packing my schedule with back-to-back clients.⁠
⁠
I was so committed to "scaling" my business to multi 6-figures and beyond that I was willing to "do whatever it took," my sanity, health, and even marriage be darned.⁠
⁠
Thus, when I found out I was pregnant with my first child, I initially panicked because though I could force my husband to put up with my foolishness, there was no way I'd be able to work at the same pace once kids came into the picture.⁠
⁠
But the more I thought about it...the more I realized that *I didn't want to.* ⁠
⁠
It's a bit embarrassing that it took having a child for me to admit it, but as a person who wanted to be a *woman in business* and not just a "businesswoman," truth be told, I WANTED time to spend on things *other* than my business, whether that be date nights with hubby, starting a garden, trying out random recipes from all my cookbooks, or now as a mom, playing "karate" with my 2 year old in the living room.⁠
⁠
Truth be told, there's a 1,001 ways to make more money but not all of them lead to more FREEDOM. ⁠
⁠
While it's true that not enough women focus on what will actually bring in money in their business (which is a discussion for a whole 'nother post), even the ones that HAVE mastered making money don't spend nearly enough time focusing on HOW they make it.⁠
⁠
Having a kid actually saved my business (and my sanity!) because it forced me to be UNREASONABLE - I only made myself available for business models that gave me more money AND more time.⁠
⁠
What about you? I meet so many women who say they "want it all" but then *give it all away* for the sake of their business. 🤦🏾‍♀️⁠
⁠
If you know how to make money in your business but don't know how to make more TIME, comment the word "READY".

Have you ever had a friend date a guy who totally didn’t appreciate her?⁠
⁠
Maybe your friend would go above and beyond - cleaning this dude’s house, updating his resume,  even filing his taxes!⁠
⁠
Yet despite all this hard work, your friend was routinely taken for granted…and maybe even cheated on. 👀😬🥴⁠
⁠
In a fit of exasperation, you’d be like “Girl! Why don’t you just leave him already!?!?”⁠
⁠
And your beautiful, brilliant, loving friend would inevitably say something to the effect of “I know I should…but I can’t…because he NEEDS me.” 🤦🏾‍♀️⁠
⁠
*Sigh.*⁠
⁠
As sad as this type of thinking is in romantic relationships…⁠
⁠
…it’s even worst in client relationships. *sips tea*⁠ ☕️ 
⁠
I can’t tell you how many beautiful, brilliant, loving women entrepreneurs I meet who LITERALLY GIVE THEIR BRILLIANCE AWAY to low paying clients who “need” what they offer…⁠
⁠
…but don’t really WANT what they offer.⁠
⁠
One of the best pieces of advice my mother gave me as teenager that served me well in dating and now, as a happily married woman, continues to serve me well in business, is this:⁠
⁠
WANT THE ONES THAT WANT YOU.⁠
⁠
Meaning…if I have to convince, cajole, and outright CHASE YOU DOWN because I know you “need” this even though it’s not clear whether or not you actually WANT this…⁠
⁠
…then issa no for me. Automatically.⁠
⁠
I only sell to those who already WANT what I have to offer, not to those who I think “need” it.⁠
⁠
Why?⁠
⁠
Because those who WANT what you have are actually *willing* to pay the price. (Are we still talking about business? 😏)⁠

If you’re like most entrepreneurs, you got into this game for FREEDOM.

Freedom do what you want and make as much as you want in the process.

The paradox I’m realizing, however, is that in order to have that freedom, you do need to follow rules.

What rules you ask?

YOUR rules!

If YOU told yourself that you need to get up by 6am everyday because you know you’re more productive when you wake up early...then you need to do that.

If YOU told yourself that you need to post every day on social media because you notice a bump in sales when you do...then you need to do that.

If YOU told yourself to stick to your prices and payment terms, even if a prospective client is asking you to change them...then you need to do that.

In other words, you have to be DISCIPLINED enough to follow your own rules for success!

For instance, I allow myself a lot of freedom, such as the ability to work from fancy locations during the day but my rule is while I’m there, *I need to actually be working.*

Entrepreneurship is not freedom from rules but the *freedom to choose your own rules.* The “catch”, however, is that you have to actually stick to them!

What rules are you going to start sticking to, no matter what?

…how different would your life look?

The truth is, you can talk yourself out of anything.

(Heck, I almost talked myself of of publishing this post!)

But imagine how amazing this coming year could be…

…if you made it your year of YES?

This is a success code that might shock you a little bit...

But once you understand this, it’ll not only help you get more out of your business but more out of life as well. 

So many entrepreneurs don’t realize that to be in business is to be in LEADERSHIP.

The story of Harriet Tubman is a perfect example of this because when she escaped slavery she didn’t just free herself. *She went back* and she lead so many other people to freedom with her. 

A lot of us are the Harriet Tubman’s of our own circle of influence. 🦸‍♀️ 

We say...

“I’ve come through this...

I’ve survived that...

I’ve succeeded in this...

...and, I don’t want other people to face the same struggles that I had so I’m going back!”🏃‍♀️

What many people don’t tell you about her story is that a lot of the people that she led to freedom…

…didn’t want to go. 👀

They told her that she was crazy, that she was going to get caught and they tried to convince her to stay.

Imagine if she had listened! 

Imagine if she had turned back because those she was leading wanted her to turn back!!

Imagine if she had followed *the very people she was supposed to be leading.*

Too many aspiring coaches and business owners have it backwards.

They say there’s somewhere DIFFERENT that they want to be…

…but then they turn around and listen to the people who are where they want to *leave*. 🤔 #howsway #makeitmakesense

Your job as a trailblazer is to lead the people - not follow the people you’re meant to lead.

⁠
I've learned long ago that while lack of sleep, lack of time, and even lack of money may all be "valid"...⁠
⁠
...it does not change the fact that *what you do with consistency matters more than what you do with intensity.*⁠
⁠
The crazy thing is that consistency is not actually hard, just inconvenient. To do something day in and day out means you have to do it on both good AND bad days.⁠
⁠
If you're looking for a breakthrough this year, commit to breaking through the belief that you need convenience in order to be consistent.

So many people focus on getting the next customer in the door...

As a mom of two young kids, those few hours in the morning are even more precious now because really my life isn't just about me anymore. 

As soon as everyone else wakes up, my energy stops pouring into me and into all my commitments, plans, and responsibilities. 

So having that quiet time in the morning to pray, do my devotional, read or sometimes just sit in silence is really important because it allows me to pour into myself BEFORE I pour into others. 

(You can't pour from an empty cup!)

So, if you're a mom like me, or really even just a woman who has to give so much of herself to other people then try out waking up early...

Not because I told you to...

And, not because so many self-made millionaires do it...

...but to give yourself the time to focus on yourself and just do you. 

So, what time are you planning on waking up tomorrow? 😏

So many entrepreneurs PREVENT their businesses from growing to the very levels they’re working so hard to reach precisely because they REFUSE to delegate!

“But I’m the only one who can do it RIGHT!”

Lies, lol. 🙄 I can’t tell you how many times I was CONVINCED that I was the only person who could do something in my business…only to finally delegate it and watch them do it way better and way *faster.*

“But I can’t afford help right now!”

If you’re saying this, that’s literally a sign you can’t afford NOT to. When I hired my executive assistant (who is U.S. based and works with me full-time btw), I wasn’t sure if I’d be able to keep paying her! But literally within the first month, she freed up so much time for me that I was able to focus on *revenue generating activities* that more than covered her cost.

“But I don’t know what to delegate!”

Start with the one tasks that has you literally pulling your hair out, no matter how small. Maybe you love the revenue webinars generate for your business but you HATE putting together the slides - delegate that. Or maybe you love the growth your email list is seeing by offering free, helpful PDFs but you hate fiddling around in Canva- delegate that.

If you’re at a point in your business where you can no longer “do it all”, then that’s a sign that *you’re not supposed to.* 

Share a piece of the pie with those who can help you and watch the pie GROW. 🥧

This strategy is what literally allowed me to quit my job!

Before then, I had done well sell low-ticket courses and digital products (think $19 eBook here, $197 masterclass there), but it wasn’t enough to give me the consistent cashflow I needed to feel comfortable quitting my job.

On top of that, I was exhausted by the sheer VOLUME of low ticket products I had to sell to replace my salary. And that’s when I realized…

If increased the value of my offer to just $2,500 or $3,500, I would only need to sell 3-4 PER MONTH (that’s 1 or so per week) to hit $10K/mo. (Say less 😎)

That’s exactly what I did and I ended up selling way more than 4 that month. In fact, I sold so many I ended up quitting my job!

If you have yet to consistently make $100K or more in your business, selling a $2,500-$3,500 package maybe the only thing standing between you and running your business full-time!

I’m convinced that every employed adult has at least ONE skill that is worth at least $25,000…otherwise you wouldn’t be employed!

Regardless of what you’re making, you can make 6-figures *in your business* by taking a skill and charging at least 10% of the value for it, i.e. at least $2,500.

✈️ I make myself available to speak internationally! And it doesn’t even have to be for a big event; last year I spoke in Turks & Caicos to an intimate group of women on *someone else’s* coaching retreat. And yes - my travel was free!

✈️ Instead of only investing my business profits in the stock market, I buy real estate *in my business name*. That makes me a real estate investor, which means I can book international trips to look at properties abroad. ✈️ I put ALL of my business expenses on travel rewards cards. So even for the times when I want to travel “just because” (like in Tel Aviv 🇮🇱), my business technically still “funds” it because I’m using the points earned from my business travel cards to travel for free! 🥂

For years, I had A LOT of limiting beliefs about about hitting the 7-figure mark in my business. For the longest, I couldn’t crack 6-figures per year. But when I got rid of these beliefs 🚮, I started experiencing 6-figure months. 👀 Let's dive into some of the biggest ones:⁠
⁠
🤔 "I need a ton of sales to make a million dollars." This is simply not true! If you have a higher priced product, you need fewer sales to hit your 7-figure goal. So don't think that you need to constantly be chasing after more and more sales in order to reach that milestone.⁠
⁠
🤔 "No one will pay me 5-figures for my work." Not all customers are focused on "saving money." Many are focused on getting the *best return for their money*. So don't sell yourself short - there are people out there who are more than willing to pay top dollar for your expertise!⁠
⁠
🤔 "I’ll have to take too much time away from my family in order to hit those numbers." The reality is, you can create a schedule and a team that supports your lifestyle. You don't have to sacrifice your family time in order to achieve big things in your business.⁠
⁠
🤔 "A million dollars is a lot of money." In the grand scheme of business, it's really not that much. There are thousands of companies that make $1 million *per day*, let alone per year. It's simply another number, and you can choose to achieve it if you want to.⁠
⁠
🤔 "My business is too small to do that kind of revenue." This is another limiting belief that can hold you back. The truth is, you don't need to build some big, behemoth corporation in order to make a lot of money in business. You can be small but mighty if you invest in the right mentorship, resources, and team⁠
⁠
🤔 "I already know what I need to do." Well, you think you do...but you don't know what you don't know! Getting high-level mentorship from coaches who were already where I wanted to be reveal that...I didn't know as much as I thought I did! 😂⁠
⁠
What beliefs are holding you back? Share with your business bestie so you can cross the 7-figure mark together!⁠

One of the biggest lies that I see perpetuated in the media about starting an online business is that you don't need to invest any money.

You could also technically get started without any money.

But, if you really want to scale your business and grow it into something that can replace your full-time job then you need to be willing to invest in your business. 

Think about a fruit tree. Before you can harvest any fruit, you need to water the tree, prune it, and protect it from birds. Eventually, all of your efforts will culminate in delicious fruit to eat. 

It's the same with any business. 👉 You need to put money into your business to get even more money out of your business. 👈

I have invested a lot in my business over the years. 

I've been full-time for six years and I've invested in my business every year, basically every quarter and sometimes every month. 

I actually had started investing in my business before I went full-time. 

The first few things that I paid for were a lot of different courses, programs, and mentors who I knew were going to help me grow my business to the level that I could do it as my full-time job.

Education was the first thing that I invested in because I wanted GUARANTEED SUCCESS. 

The beauty of investing in your education is that, unlike the stock market, there is no chance of loss. 

You will always get a return from investing in education. 

What's more, is that you're also guaranteed to grow your business... 
✅ Faster...
✅ More efficiently... 
✅ And, more effectively...
...if you invest in your education.

With all that in mind, I don't see any reason to hesitate about investing in your business. 

Open up your wallets and watch your seedling blossom into a bountiful fruit tree. 🌳

Business owners often fall into a trap 😵‍💫, thinking they'll hire *after* reaching a certain revenue level.

*sigh*

To actually reach that income, you NEED to make that hire first! You need that support to ELEVATE your business.

Hitting a revenue ceiling? The answer might be to bring someone on.👈

I was TERRIFIED😫 to hire my first full-time executive assistant last year, but I was burnt out. I put off hiring for MONTHS.

It took a 55k mastermind with multimillionaires to make me realize the importance of taking that leap.

I did it anyway because sometimes, those ahead of you tell you to make moves that you don't fully understand... but if you understood them, you'd already be on their level.👀

I hired my assistant last year, and I honestly don't know how I functioned without her. She's freed up my time and allowed me to fully step into my CEO role.

Imagine if I'd listened to that voice saying I "couldn't afford her"!🤦‍♀️

Remember, it's not that you can't afford to hire; it's that you can't afford *not* to hire.👈

So many established coaches get this wrong and are TERRIFIED of raising their prices.

*sigh*

You’ve gotten more experience. Your following is bigger. You know you can get your clients the results they want faster and more effectively than before, but...

...You’re afraid that if you raise your prices you’ll lose your clients. 

Does this sound like you? 👀

What I mean is that your clients aren’t picking you because of your prices...

...They’re picking you for YOU. 🫵

(Specifically, they’re choosing you because of the RETURN that they see themselves getting from working with you.)

I didn’t mind spending nearly $60k to join a mastermind because it was filled with multi-millionaires. - I trusted they would teach me how to parlay that investment into $700k. 

However, I won’t spend $197 on a program that promises to help me revamp my YouTube channel and turn it into a magnet for new clients and followers. - It was offering so much for too little so I didn’t trust it. 🤔

(Both of these are #truestories btw.)

Therefore, if you want people to pay more, then offer more.

 It’s as simple as that. 😎
